## 1. Executive Summary

**ReelBid** is a full-stack, real-time online auction platform built specifically for **premium movie memorabilia**. The platform enables collectors (Buyers) to bid on exclusive items listed by verified sellers, with comprehensive administrative oversight ensuring platform integrity and trust.

The platform operates on a **three-pillar role-based ecosystem**:
- **Buyers** ŌĆö Register, fund their wallet, browse auctions, place bids, and complete payments for won items.
- **Sellers** ŌĆö List authentic movie memorabilia, monitor auction progress, manage post-auction payment collection, and handle second-chance offers.
- **Admins** ŌĆö Oversee the entire platform including user management, role assignments, financial oversight, tier management, and withdrawal approvals.

### Key Highlights
| Feature | Description |
|---|---|
| **Real-Time Bidding** | WebSocket-powered live bid updates across all connected clients |
| **Sniper Protection** | Automatic 1-hour auction extension if a bid arrives in the last 10 minutes |
| **Wallet & Tier System** | Secure wallet with tier classification based on deposit balance (display/classification only ŌĆö not enforced as bid limits) |
| **HMAC Wallet Integrity** | Server-side cryptographic hash verification prevents balance tampering |
| **Security Deposits** | Dynamic deposit calculation with automatic lock/unlock/refund workflows |
| **Razorpay Integration** | Secure payment gateway for winner payment completion |
| **Second-Chance Offers** | Seller can offer the item to runner-up bidders if the winner defaults |
| **Profanity Filtering** | Comprehensive multi-language content filter (English + Hindi) |
| **Email Notifications** | Automated emails for payment reminders, auction extensions, and second-chance offers |

---

## 2. Project Overview

### 2.1 Purpose
ReelBid aims to create a trusted marketplace for movie memorabilia collectors, ensuring authenticity through seller verification, fair bidding through anti-sniper protection, and financial safety through a secure wallet system with cryptographic integrity checks.

### 2.2 Target Users
| User Type | Description |
|---|---|
| **Collectors / Buyers** | Movie memorabilia enthusiasts looking to acquire rare props, costumes, posters, and other cinematic artifacts |
| **Sellers** | Verified individuals or organizations possessing authentic movie memorabilia |
| **Platform Administrators** | Internal staff managing platform operations, user roles, and financial workflows |

### 2.3 Scope
The platform covers the complete auction lifecycle:
- User registration and profile completion
- Wallet funding and tier assignment
- Auction creation, real-time bidding, and completion
- Post-auction payment collection (online via Razorpay or cash)
- Security deposit management (lock, unlock, refund)
- Withdrawal request and admin approval
- Second-chance offer workflow for defaulting winners

---

## 3. Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Framework** | Next.js 16.1.6 (React 19.2) | Full-stack React framework with SSR and API routes |
| **Language** | TypeScript 5 | Type-safe JavaScript for both client and server |
| **Database** | MongoDB (via Mongoose 9.2) | NoSQL document database for flexible schema |
| **Authentication** | NextAuth.js 4.24 | OAuth (Google) + Credentials (OTP/Password) authentication |
| **Real-Time** | Socket.IO 4.8 | WebSocket-based real-time bidding updates |
| **Payments** | Razorpay 2.9 | Secure online payment gateway (INR) |
| **Email** | Nodemailer 7.0 | Transactional email delivery for notifications |
| **UI Components** | Lucide React 0.575 | Modern icon library |
| **Animations** | Framer Motion 12.34 | UI animations and transitions |
| **Styling** | Vanilla CSS with CSS Variables | Custom design system with dark/light theme support |
| **State** | React Hot Toast 2.6 | Toast notifications for user feedback |
| **Custom Server** | tsx + HTTP + Socket.IO | Custom Node.js server for WebSocket support alongside Next.js |

