## 4. System Architecture

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Client["Frontend (React/Next.js)"]
        HP["Home Page"]
        AP["Auction Pages"]
        BD["Buyer Dashboard"]
        SD["Seller Dashboard"]
        AD["Admin Dashboard"]
        LB["Leaderboard"]
        WP["Working Process"]
    end

    subgraph Server["Backend (Next.js API Routes)"]
        AUTH["Auth API (NextAuth)"]
        BIDS["Bids API"]
        WALLET["Wallet API"]
        ITEMS["Items API"]
        ADMIN_API["Admin API"]
        SELLER_API["Seller API"]
        PAYMENT["Payment API"]
        OTP_API["OTP API"]
    end

    subgraph Services["External Services"]
        RAZORPAY["Razorpay Payment Gateway"]
        SMTP["SMTP Email Server"]
        GOOGLE["Google OAuth"]
    end

    subgraph Data["Data Layer"]
        MONGO["MongoDB"]
        SOCKET["Socket.IO Server"]
    end

    Client --> Server
    Server --> MONGO
    Server --> RAZORPAY
    Server --> SMTP
    AUTH --> GOOGLE
    SOCKET --> Client
    BIDS --> SOCKET
```

### 4.1 Architecture Pattern
- **Monolithic Full-Stack**: Single Next.js application with API routes serving as the backend
- **Custom Server**: HTTP server wraps Next.js with Socket.IO for real-time bidding
- **JWT Sessions**: Stateless authentication using JSON Web Tokens
- **Server-Side Validation**: All financial operations validated exclusively on the server
- **HMAC Wallet Integrity**: Cryptographic hash verification on every wallet mutation

