#### 7.2.1 Tier System (Classification Only)

Tiers are a **classification/display feature** assigned automatically based on wallet balance. Each tier has a `name`, `minBalance`, `bidLimit`, and `order` stored in the database. However, the `bidLimit` field is **NOT currently enforced** during bid placement ŌĆö it exists in the data model for potential future enforcement.

| Tier | Minimum Balance | Bid Limit (Not Enforced) |
|---|---|---|
| None | Ōé╣0 | ŌĆö |
| Tier A (Example) | Ōé╣100 | Ōé╣10,000 |
| Tier B (Example) | Ōé╣500 | Ōé╣1,00,000 |
| Tier C (Example) | Ōé╣1,000 | Ōé╣10,00,000 |

> [!NOTE]
> Tiers are fully dynamic and configured by the Admin. The above values are illustrative defaults.
> **Current Status:** Tiers are assigned on wallet top-up and displayed on user profiles/dashboards, but the `bidLimit` is not checked when placing bids. Bidding is restricted only by available wallet balance for security deposits.

